    pearls: ["Premature discontinuation of DAPT after coronary stent placement is the strongest risk factor for stent thrombosis -- educate patients never to stop without cardiology consultation","CYP2C19 pharmacogenomic testing is now recommended before initiating clopidogrel; poor metabolizers should receive ticagrelor or prasugrel instead","Ticagrelor is direct-acting (not a prodrug) and provides more consistent platelet inhibition than clopidogrel, but requires twice-daily dosing and causes dyspnea in ~14% of patients","Prasugrel is contraindicated in patients with prior stroke/TIA (increased intracranial bleeding risk) and in patients >75 years or <60 kg (generally unfavorable risk-benefit)","When a patient on DAPT requires urgent surgery, weigh bleeding risk vs. stent thrombosis risk; if surgery cannot be delayed, continue aspirin and hold the P2Y12 inhibitor for the minimum safe interval"],
