    pearls: ["APA/ADA consensus guidelines recommend metabolic monitoring at baseline, 4 weeks, 8 weeks, 12 weeks, then quarterly for weight/BMI and annually for fasting glucose, HbA1c, and lipid panel","Clozapine and olanzapine carry the HIGHEST metabolic risk; aripiprazole and ziprasidone carry the LOWEST -- consider metabolic profile when selecting an antipsychotic","A weight gain of >7% from baseline is clinically significant and warrants intervention: lifestyle modification, metformin adjunct, or antipsychotic switch","Antipsychotic-induced diabetes can present as DKA (especially with clozapine) -- educate patients on hyperglycemia symptoms: polyuria, polydipsia, weight loss, fatigue","Metabolic syndrome (3 of 5 criteria: central obesity, elevated triglycerides, low HDL, elevated BP, elevated fasting glucose) significantly increases cardiovascular mortality in patients on antipsychotics"],
